        <mxCell id="leg7" parent="1" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;fontSize=10;fontColor=#666666;" value="Lanes: storage edges route&#xa;through the right channel;&#xa;crossings are perpendicular." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="44" width="150" x="2030" y="615" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="decisions" parent="1" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#FFF2CC;strokeColor=#D6B656;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontStyle=1;fontSize=14;spacingLeft=16;spacingTop=10;" value="Key Architectural Decisions &amp; Hard Rules  (RFC-000…004 · ADR-001…005)" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="150" width="1800" x="60" y="1820" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="dec_l" parent="1" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=12;spacingLeft=10;" value="• HR1 — Never claim vectorless/tree RAG beats vector RAG on accuracy; position on architecture only.&#xa;• HR2 — Erasure cascades across ALL derived stores in order (see cascade note).&#xa;• HR3 — PII routes only through no-training + ZDR tier; OPENAI_BASE_URL is the lever; self-host is the floor.&#xa;• HR4 — AGPL awareness: PyMuPDF enters via 3 transitive pullers; outline reader moved to pypdfium2 (RFC-004 Q2, landed).&#xa;• HR5 — validate_tree() runs before save_doc; failing tree never persists (raises low_quality_tree)." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="110" width="900" x="80" y="1860" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="dec_r" parent="1" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=12;spacingLeft=10;" value="• PDF extraction is markdown-first; Docling (MIT) primary, pymupdf4llm AGPL fallback — fixes ﬂ-ligature garbling.&#xa;• Flat docs are a SUCCESS route (node_count&lt;3 / depth&lt;2 → flat.json); garbling is the SOLE terminal reject.&#xa;• VLM hierarchy detection designed but VLM_MODE=disabled (DPI-unstable); Granite-258M rejected (user-locked).&#xa;• Converter runs in subprocess (Docling +237MB/doc in-process leak; OOM isolation).&#xa;• LLM-01 provider abstraction (PR #10) + LLM-02 Langfuse tracing (PR #11) — both paths, one project, cost." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="110" width="860" x="1000" y="1860" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
